Privacy Policy
Wera Werkzeuge GmbH
We take the protection of your personal data very seriously. We always treat your personal data in accordance with the statutory data protection regulations. We have appointed a competent and reliable external data protection officer.
We inform you below about the processing of your personal data.
Collection and processing of personal data on our website
You can use our online services without revealing your identity. Should we request personal data (such as name, address or e-mail address) on our website, e.g. in the context of contact forms or when registering, this is done on a voluntary basis. We use this information exclusively for our own business purposes (such as the shipment of requested materials/information).
For any questions you may have, we offer you the opportunity to contact us via a form provided on the website. Data marked as mandatory is required in order to be able to process the request. Further information can be provided voluntarily. Data processing in the purpose of contacting us is carried out as per point (a) of Article 6(1) GDPR based on your voluntarily granted consent.
The personal data collected while using the contact form will be deleted after your request is completed and after expiry of the fiscal and commercial retention obligations.
Once you have given your consent - for example to receive a newsletter or other interesting information from our company - you can revoke it at any time without stating any reason. The revocation of consent does not affect the legality of the processing carried out on the basis of the consent until the revocation. You can do so via the above mentioned contact form or any other way mentioned in the newsletter.
This site uses "cookies". Cookies are text files that are stored on your computer and that allow an analysis of the use of the website. You can prevent the installation of cookies by setting your browser accordingly.
No other techniques are used that allow conclusions to be drawn on the basis of the behaviour of users.
Logging on the website
Each time you access the website, logs are created and processed for statistical purposes, leaving the individual user anonymous:
Referrer (page via whose link you came to this website)
Search terms (act as referrer in search engines)
IP is evaluated to determine the country of origin and the provider
Browser, operating system, installed plug- ins and screen resolution
Time spent on the page
The data above are processed on the basis of our legitimate interest as per point (f) of Article 6(1) GDPR for the following purposes:
Ensuring a smooth Internet connection on our website
Ensuring comfortable use of our website
Evaluation of system security and stability as well as
for further administrative purposes.
We reserve the right to check this data subsequently when we become aware of specific indications of illegal use. The data will be deleted immediately when no longer necessary to attain the purpose.
Circulation of data
Circulation to third parties, for commercial or non-commercial purposes, will generally not take place without your explicit consent. We only circulate your personal data to third parties in exceptional cases and only if permitted and/or required by law [e.g. on the basis of Article 6 GDPR]. In part, we use service providers for the statutory order processing of data; e.g. our website is hosted by Plusnet GmbH. Full responsibility for data processing remains with us.
Storage and erasure of data
Your data will be kept as long as necessary for the respective purposes mentioned above. The data will be deleted at the latest after the termination of the contractual relationship and after expiry of the legal retention periods of the civil, commercial and tax law.
Rights of the data subject
We hereby inform you that as per Article 15 et seqq GDPR under the conditions defined there you have the right of information about the personal data concerned, as well as the right to rectification or erasure of data, the right to restriction of processing or a right to object to the processing as well as the right of data portability. You also have the right to appeal to a data protection supervisory authority as per Article 77 GDPR if you believe that the processing of your personal data infringes this regulation. If the processing is based on point (a) of Article 6(1) GDPR or point (a) of Article 9(2) GDPR, you also have the right to revoke your consent at any time without affecting the legality of the processing carried out on the basis of your consent until your revocation.
Right of access, Art. 15
GDPR
You have the right to request information as to whether and to what extent your personal data is processed (in particular processing purpose, recipient of the data, duration of storage, etc).
Right to rectification, Art. 16
GDPR
You have the right to request the correction of your stored data if they are inaccurate or incomplete. This includes the right to provide supplementary statements or messages to help the completion of said data.
Right of erasure, Art. 17
GDPR
You have the right to request the erasure of your personal data. This is possible, for example, if the data are no longer required for the purposes for which they were collected or if the data should be deleted due to legal obligations. In individual cases, however, this right may be excluded.
Right to restriction of processing, Art. 18
GDPR
You have the right to restriction of the processing of your personal data. This is possible, for example, if your data are incorrectly recorded or the data processing is unlawful. If the processing is restricted, the data may only be processed in narrowly defined cases.
Right of data portability, Art. 20
GDPR
You have the right to demand that we provide the data concerning you in a standard electronic, machine-readable format to you or to any person you designate if you provided these data yourself.
Right to object, Art. 21 GDPR
You have the right, on grounds relating to your particular situation, to object to the processing of personal data concerning you at any time with effect for the future, provided that data processing takes place in protection of legitimate interests (see points (e) and (f) of Article 6(1) GDPR). In case of your objection, we will check whether the legal requirements for the processing of your data is met and, if this is not the case, refrain from any further processing of your data.
Right to complain to the Data Protection Supervisory Authority, Art. 77
GDPR
You have the right to contact the competent supervisory authority of the Union or the Member States at any time for possible violations of data protection regulations.
Liability for our own content
The content of this website was compiled with the highest care. However, we cannot guarantee the accuracy, completeness and timeliness of the content. As the operator of this website, we are responsible for our own content on these pages according to applicable general laws.
Liability for links
Cross-references ("links") to content provided by other providers should be distinguished from our own content and treated separately. We have no influence on content provided in third party links; the content of the linked pages is always the responsibility of the respective provider or operator of the pages. In this respect, we provide "foreign content" only when labelled as such (as “external”).
Links are always dynamic references. Upon initial insertion of links, we check the third party content for possible civil or criminal liability to ensure illegal content was not identified at the time of linking. However, it is not possible to permanently check the external content of linked pages for changes that may give rise to responsibility. We always strive to ensure control within reason. If we find or have been advised that a specific offer to which a link is made trigger a civil or criminal liability, we will immediately remove the reference to this offer. If you find dubious content on any of our linked sites, please contact us.
Change of our Privacy Policy
We reserve the right to change this Privacy Policy from time to time to comply with current legal requirements or to implement changes to our services in the Privacy Policy, for example, when introducing new services. Further visits to our website will be subject to the new Privacy Policy.
Questions
If you have any questions regarding the processing of your personal data, you can contact our data protection officer directly, who and whose team are also available for requests, information or complaints.
Contact our Data Protection Officer
UIMC Dr. Vossbein GmbH & Co. KG, DPO
Email: datenschutz.wera[at]uimc.de
We process the personal data with regard to you as an individual to prepare offers and to fulfil the contracts as per point (f) of Article 6(1) GDPR. Processing for the purpose of accounting and costing as well as for the fulfilment of legal obligations (for example, commercial and tax law) is based on point (c) of Article 6(1) GDPR. The business relationship exists between us and your company. If you act as an individual legal entity (e.g. as a sole trader or self-employed), your data will be processed to perform pre-contractual action and fulfilment of contracts on the legal basis of point (b) of Article 6(1) GDPR.
In case you have contacted one of our customers as the data subject or are in business relations with them, we may have received your data from our client as part of our service agreement with them. In this case we process your data only when and as far as it is necessary to process the specific request. Data processing in such cases takes place in the legitimate interest of a third party (our customer), consisting of technical improvement in data protection procedures and optimization of our processes. Their interests, fundamental rights and freedoms are duly taken into account.
Furthermore, data can also be processed for authorized purposes as per point (f) of Article 6(1) GDPR, such as marketing, internal market research and marketing purposes, and for gathering in-house statistics. Such legitimate interests include the optimization of processes and attributions in line with the cost; while your interests, fundamental rights and freedoms are duly taken into account.
Only if you have given us your consent, or if we have informed you fairly in the context of data collection as per § 7 UWG (Gesetz gegen den unlauteren Wettbewerb = Act against unfair competition), we may use your data to send you information about products, services, events and other things worth knowing about us. You can unsubscribe from such communications at any time with immediate effect. The revocation of consent does not affect the legality of the processing carried out on the basis of the consent until the revocation.
Circulation of data
Circulation to third parties, for commercial or non-commercial purposes, will generally not take place without your explicit consent. We only pass on your personal data to third parties in exceptional cases and only if permitted by law [e.g. on the basis of Article 6 GDPR] and/or required in the context of the above-mentioned business relationships.
In order to be able to offer you information and services optimal for the above-mentioned purposes in the context of the business relationship, information on said contractual relationships (including personal data) will be passed on internally within Wera Werkzeuge GmbH. In some cases, external service providers can have access to your data (IT, file/disk destruction, tax consultant, lawyer).
Storage and erasure of data
Your data will be kept as long as necessary for the respective purposes mentioned above. The data will be deleted at the latest after the termination of the contractual relationship and after expiry of the operational and legal retention periods of the civil, commercial and tax law.
Rights of the data subject
We hereby inform you that as per Article 15 et seqq GDPR under the conditions defined there you have the right of information about the personal data concerned, as well as the right to rectification or erasure of data, the right to restriction of processing or a right to object to the processing as well as the right of data portability. You also have the right to appeal to a data protection supervisory authority as per Article 77 GDPR if you believe that the processing of your personal data infringes this regulation. If the processing is based on point (a) of Article 6(1) GDPR or point (a) of Article 9(2) GDPR, you also have the right to revoke your consent at any time without affecting the legality of the processing carried out on the basis of your consent until your revocation.
Right of access, Art. 15
GDPR
You have the right to request information as to whether and to what extent your personal data is processed (in particular processing purpose, recipient of the data, duration of storage, etc).
Right to rectification, Art. 16
GDPR
You have the right to request the correction of your stored data if they are inaccurate or incomplete. This includes the right to provide supplementary statements or messages to help the completion of said data.
Right of erasure, Art. 17
GDPR
You have the right to request the erasure of your personal data. This is possible, for example, if the data are no longer required for the purposes for which they were collected or if the data should be deleted due to legal obligations. In individual cases, however, this right may be excluded.
Right to restriction of processing, Art. 18
GDPR
You have the right to restriction of the processing of your personal data. This is possible, for example, if your data are incorrectly recorded or the data processing is unlawful. If the processing is restricted, the data may only be processed in narrowly defined cases.
Right of data portability, Art. 20
GDPR
You have the right to demand that we provide the data concerning you in a standard electronic, machine-readable format to you or to any person you designate if you provided these data yourself.
Right to object, Art. 21 GDPR
You have the right, on grounds relating to your particular situation, to object to the processing of personal data concerning you at any time with effect for the future, provided that data processing takes place in protection of legitimate interests (see points (e) and (f) of Article 6(1) GDPR). In case of your objection, we will check whether the legal requirements for the processing of your data is met and, if this is not the case, refrain from any further processing of your data.
Right to complain to the Data Protection Supervisory Authority, Art. 77
GDPR
You have the right to contact the competent supervisory authority of the Union or the Member States at any time for possible violations of data protection regulations.
Change of our Privacy Policy
We reserve the right to change this Privacy Policy from time to time to comply with current legal requirements or to implement changes to our services in the Privacy Policy, for example, when introducing new services. Further visits to our website will be subject to the new Privacy Policy.
Questions
If you have any questions regarding the processing of your personal data, you can contact our data protection officer directly, who and whose team are also available for requests, information or complaints.
Contact our Data Protection Officer
UIMC Dr. Vossbein GmbH & Co. KG, DPO
Email: datenschutz.wera[at]uimc.de
We process your personal information in connection with conducting your application procedure and to examine your potential work-related applicability. We process the information you provided for the purpose of a well-informed employment decision based on GDPR Art. 6 §1(b). In addition, employment assessments are stored on the basis of objective, non-discriminatory criteria; if this is permissible on a case-by-case basis, publicly accessible personal data about yourself will also be stored.
The data you provide are required to complete the application process. Without these data we cannot consider your application.
Circulation/Service providers
Only if you have given consent will we pass on your personal data to other companies in our group to provide you with further employment options within said group of companies.
Some of your personal data will be passed on to external service providers (e.g. tax consultants, legal advisers). In some cases, external IT service providers (as part of order data processing as per GDPR Article 28) can access your data. In such circumstances the service providers are bound by instructions, which was secured through contracts accordingly.
Storage and deletion of data
Your data will be kept for as long as necessary for the above purposes of the recruitment process. If you object to data processing during the recruitment process, the data will be deleted - unless contrary to other statutory retention requirements.
The data will be deleted after completion of the application process and after expiration of any time limit, unless you have given your consent to save your application for further job opportunities. Unsolicited applications will be saved until their revocation, or up to two years, and then deleted.
Your rights
We inform you that as per Article 15 et seqq GDPR under the conditions defined there you have the following rights of the data subject: right to information about the personal data concerned, right to rectification or erasure of data, right to restriction of processing or a right to object to the processing as well as the right of data portability. You also have the right to complain to a data protection supervisory authority as per Article 77 GDPR. If the processing is based on point (a) of Article 6(1) GDPR or point (a) of Article 9(2) GDPR, you also have the right to revoke your consent at any time without affecting the legality of the processing carried out until your revocation.
